{"id": "1444452341364424889", "channel_id": "1444265958448431236", "type": 19, "author_id": "1437487264023318668", "author_name": "vxvendetta97", "author_bot": false, "content": "I already given a possible suggestion that could help to make the raids more enjoyable to Light, like this:\n\n- You can get more rewards for the first clear of the day, and a bit less on each subsequent one (with a possible cap for the silver and rare material after the 5th or something);\n- Each boss has a tot of clears needed to be defeated, when the community reach the collective goal, all get a reward (you can still fight it to have the base rewards until the event end, with a minimum duration of tot weeks or\\and a possible cap for a single stage).\n\nTo make it less time consuming, make it more collaborative, and to limit the sense of frustration because of new players that think that they are missing out on potential rewards because they don't have a lot of unit to use, or others that have the compulsion to clear it as much as possible during a day because they think that they would waste precious resources otherwise.\n\nBut after experiencing the raid, will gather more opinions and discuss the best possible approaches for the future, and present them to him.", "timestamp": "2025-11-29T22:17:54.808000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-11-29T22:18:26.780000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": ["1154601435141509192"], "reactions": [{"emoji": "point", "emoji_id": "1356053112292511815", "count": 2}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1444450902932197557", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1444265958448431236", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "V2.4.0.7 版本前瞻 ┊ Version Outlook", "forum_channel_id": "1355085076500578363", "thread_tags": ["1357267957901951088", "1357267999253467207"]}
